The abducted chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Orhionmwon Local Government Area of Edo State, Godwin Aigbogun, yesterday escaped from his abductors in the forest. Our reporter gathered that the victim played along as the abductors were insisting on the payment of N5 million ransom.   ‘Kerosene price rose by 12.09% in June’     Dockworkers shut terminals     CAF AWARDS 2022: Oshoala may pick record fifth African …   Edo Publicity Secretary of APC, Peter Uwadia-Igbinigie,  who confirmed the escape of Aigbogun, said that he was hale and hearty. Uwadia-Igbinigie said: “I can confirm to you that he has escaped from the kidnappers’ den. I must commend him for his bravery. “The APC family in Edo State is happy about this. He is now with his family.”